.@CDCgov webinar: #hemophilia inhibitor patients are twice as likely to be hospitalized as non inhibitor patients. #bleedingdisorders
.@CDCgov webinbar: there is a 70% higher death rate for those w/#hemophilia & inhibitors vs. those without inhibitors. #bleedingdisorders
.@CDCgov webinar: first inhibitor testing was in 1959 in the UK. #hemophilia, #bleedingdisorders
RT @hemophiliafed: .@CDCgov webinar: first inhibitor testing was in 1959 in the UK. #hemophilia, #bleedingdisorders
.@CDCgov webinar: #Hemophilia Inhibitor Research Study (HIRS) collected treatment data for 1,000 patients and followed them for 3 years.
.@CDCgov webinar: HIRS study showed that all patients with #hemophilia are at risk for developing inhibitors. #bleedingdisorders
.@CDCgov webinar: HIRS Study showed that 1/3 of newly-developed inhibitors were found in people with non-severe #hemophilia patients.
.@CDCgov webinar: HIRS Study six out of ten #hemophilia patients who tested for an inhibitor had no symptoms. #bleedingdisorders
.@CDC webinar: Since there is no effective monitoring system, the actual number of people w/#hemophilia & inhibitors in US is not known.
.@CDC Webinar: About 60% of people w/#hemophilia & inhibitors do not have symptoms, but may develop problems from an undetected inhibitor.
.@CDCgov webinar: HIRS study showed that people with #hemophilia of all ages are at risk for developing an inhibitor.
.@CDC webinar: Unless #hemophilia patients are tested for an inhibitor regularly, they may not know it until it causes bleeding problems.
.@CDC webinar: People w/#hemophilia receiving care in federally funded hemophilia treatment centers will be tested yearly for an inhibitor
.@CDC gov: Up to 1/5 people w/#hemophilia will develop an inhibitor to the infused factor that is used to treat bleeding. #bleedingdisorders
.@CDC webinar: There is still much to learn about inhibitors & how to prevent inhibitors. #hemophilia, #bleedingdisorders
